President Uhuru Kenyatta has sent a message of condolence to President Tomislav Nikoli and the people of Serbia, following the death of Serbian Ambassador Ivan Zivkovic. The envoy on Monday evening while undergoing treatment in Nairobi. Uhuru said Ambassador Zivkovic s death is not only a blow to his country, but also to Kenya. Since his posting to Kenya, Zivkovic has been working tirelessly to improve bilateral and trade relations between the two countries. Uhuru said Zivkovic strongly advocated for education and helped increase the number of scholarships awarded to the Kenyan youth by the Serbian government.